<subSubSection pageId="155" pageNumber="757" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="155.[702,1295,1877,2296]" lastBlockId="155.[91,1296,2303,2731]" pageId="155" pageNumber="757">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[703,983,2066,2100]" pageId="155" pageNumber="757">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 140-162 mm, tail 112-135 mm, ear 20-25 mm, hindfoot 25-31 mm; weight 60-120 g. No specific data are available for body weight. A medium-sized rat, Thomas's Rock Rat has fur grizzled reddish brown dorsally and grayish white ventrally. Ears are rounded and reddish brown. Tail is relatively long (c.106% of head—body length) and scaled, covered with short stiff hairs, and uniformly brown. Limbs are short and stout, with four digits on forefoot and five digits on hindfoot.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
